LineNo: 12659149,

Narrator: Together with the parliament, we we...
en


Together with the parliament, we were going to declare the new constitution to the whole kingdom -- appointing a new government and a head of state. It was a big day.

LineNo: 12659251,

Narrator: I was told that after the announcem...
en


I was told that after the announcement made by Manus, thousands of people had already gathered in the plaza near the House, in anticipation of today's spectacle.

LineNo: 12660465,

Narrator: It was early in the morning. We wer...
en


It was early in the morning. We were driving in a sleek, black car adorned with the royal crest, towards the House of Delegates.

LineNo: 12660845,

Narrator: I was told that despite not making...
en


I was told that despite not making a big announcement, hundreds of people had gathered in the plaza near the House, expecting our arrival.

LineNo: 12660947,

Narrator: The convoy then turned onto a grand...
en


The convoy then turned onto a grand boulevard, lined with quince trees and cutting through Porte Drazon at its center, leading directly to the Old Town.

LineNo: 12668135,

Narrator: The sidewalks were mostly empty, ex...
en


The sidewalks were mostly empty, except for the street vendors who were preparing to showcase their wares. It was an eerily quiet morning.

LineNo: 12668237,

Narrator: The sidewalks were slowly coming to...
en


The sidewalks were slowly coming to life, with street vendors preparing to showcase their wares, and large groups of people walking towards the parliament with Rizian flags in their hands.

LineNo: 12668339,

Narrator: Titus, seated next to the driver, r...
en


Titus, seated next to the driver, received a radio message. After listening to it, he turned his head towards me and pulled down the screen between us.

LineNo: 12668441,

Titus Gordion: Yes. That's what we were told, You...
en


"Yes. That's what we were told, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 12668639,

Titus Gordion: Your Majesty. Due to a massive gat...
en


"Your Majesty. Due to a massive gathering just outside the parliament, we're being redirected towards the second entrance of the House of Delegates."

LineNo: 12668741,

Titus Gordion: Your Majesty. We've just received...
en


"Your Majesty. We've just received word from the security. The entrance to the House of Delegates is clear."

LineNo: 12668843,

Titus Gordion: We'll be proceeding to enter the c...
en


"We'll be proceeding to enter the complex from the Silver Gate within a couple minutes."

LineNo: 12668969,

Player_Romus: Thanks for telling me.
en


"Thanks for telling me."

LineNo: 12669071,

Player_Romus: I hope nothing's wrong.
en


"I hope nothing's wrong."

LineNo: 12669173,

Player_Romus: Finally.
en


"Finally."

LineNo: 12669275,

Player_Romus: I am very nervous, Titus.
en


"I am very nervous, Titus."

LineNo: 12669377,

Titus Gordion: I understand it's a big day, Your...
en


"I understand it's a big day, Your Majesty. Please don't worry."

LineNo: 12669479,

Narrator: He bowed his head.
en


He bowed his head.

LineNo: 12669581,

Narrator: The parliament building came into v...
en


The parliament building came into view, its plain facade adorned with flags and symbols of the nation's heritage, shining in the middle of the empty streets.

LineNo: 12669683,

Titus Gordion: Not at all, Your Majesty. Everythi...
en


"Not at all, Your Majesty. Everything is under control."

LineNo: 12670063,

Narrator: As the convoy neared the House of D...
en


As the convoy neared the House of Delegates, the crowds and their chants thickened. Banners fluttered in the breeze, praising me for my selfless support for democracy.

LineNo: 12670443,

Narrator: As the convoy neared the House of D...
en


As the convoy neared the House of Delegates, the crowds and their chants thickened. Banners fluttered in the breeze, demanding change and reform in Rizia.

LineNo: 12670823,

Narrator: As the car pulled up to the entranc...
en


As the car pulled up to the entrance of the House of Delegates, I took a deep breath, steeling myself for the ceremony ahead.

LineNo: 12673917,

Player_Romus: Didn't you say there was a massive...
en


"Didn't you say there was a massive gathering?"

LineNo: 12674019,

Player_Romus: There is nobody around the House o...
en


"There is nobody around the House of Delegates. Why are we being directed to the Silver Gate again?"

LineNo: 12674121,

Narrator: From my view, I could barely see th...
en


From my view, I could barely see the Golden Gate, the main entrance of the parliamentary complex. However, there was no crowd waiting for us there.

LineNo: 12674239,

Player_Romus_Italic: I kept my thoughts to myself as we...
en


I kept my thoughts to myself as we kept driving towards the building.

LineNo: 12674245,

Player_Romus_Italic: I kept my thoughts to myself as we...
Menu Text en


Don't remark on it.

LineNo: 12674347,

Titus Gordion: We were told to approach from the...
en


"We were told to approach from the southern side of the building for security reasons, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 12674449,

Titus Gordion: We'll be proceeding to enter the c...
en


"We'll be proceeding to enter the complex from the Golden Gate within a couple minutes."

LineNo: 12674567,

Narrator: Instead of going forward to the mai...
en


Instead of going forward to the main entrance, the convoy took a turn before reaching the parliament.

LineNo: 12674669,

Narrator: The side street we were in was alre...
en


The side street we were in was already cleared of any bystanders. There was nobody on the street apart from a few policemen.

LineNo: 12674771,

Narrator: As we reached the end of the street...
en


As we reached the end of the street, the convoy stopped. I noticed Titus and the driver were receiving messages from their earpieces.

LineNo: 12674873,

Titus Gordion: Your Majesty. We are on hold until...
en


"Your Majesty. We are on hold until the police clear the way to the Silver Gate."

LineNo: 12674991,

Player_Romus: Thanks for telling me, Titus. Is t...
en


"Thanks for telling me, Titus. Is there something to be worried about?"

LineNo: 12675093,

Player_Romus: What's wrong?
en


"What's wrong?"

LineNo: 12675195,

Player_Romus_Italic: I nodded.
en


I nodded.

LineNo: 12675201,

Player_Romus_Italic: I nodded.
Menu Text en


Nod.

LineNo: 12675303,

Titus Gordion: Nothing, sir.
en


"Nothing, sir."

LineNo: 12675405,

Titus Gordion: The police said they have to make...
en


"The police said they have to make sure there is no security risk for our convoy before letting us through."

LineNo: 12675507,

Narrator: After a few minutes passed, Titus m...
en


After a few minutes passed, Titus made a sign and called out to the police officer, who was standing in front of the convoy.

LineNo: 12675609,

Narrator: She came to us with quick steps. Ti...
en


She came to us with quick steps. Titus lowered the window on his side of the car to speak with her.

LineNo: 12675711,

Titus Gordion: What's taking so long? The King ne...
en


"What's taking so long? The King needs to join a session at the House of Delegates."

LineNo: 12675813,

Narrator: The officer leaned in: Sir. The en...
en


The officer leaned in: "Sir. The entrance hasn't been cleared yet."

LineNo: 12675915,

Narrator: We are waiting for additional forc...
en


"We are waiting for additional forces to arrive before clearing the entrance."

LineNo: 12676017,

Titus Gordion: Will it take long?
en


"Will it take long?"

LineNo: 12676119,

Narrator: No, sir. We just need a few more m...
en


"No, sir. We just need a few more minutes."

LineNo: 12676221,

Narrator: I checked my pocket watch. We were...
en


I checked my pocket watch. We were already late for the signing.

LineNo: 12676339,

Player_Romus: Titus. Tell the police to let us t...
en


"Titus. Tell the police to let us through. I don't care about the security risks. This is the King's order."

LineNo: 12676441,

Player_Romus_Italic: I waited patiently.
en


I waited patiently.

LineNo: 12676447,

Player_Romus_Italic: I waited patiently.
Menu Text en


Wait patiently.

LineNo: 12676549,

Player_Romus: Titus. Tell the convoy that we're...
en


"Titus. Tell the convoy that we're going back to the palace."

LineNo: 12676651,

Titus Gordion: I'm pretty sure you heard that.
en


"I'm pretty sure you heard that."

LineNo: 12676753,

Narrator: He nodded and turned back to the of...
en


He nodded and turned back to the officer.

LineNo: 12676855,

Titus Gordion: Your Majesty. I don't know how we...
en


"Your Majesty. I don't know how we turn the entire convoy in this small street."

LineNo: 12676957,

Narrator: He gestured at the Golden Guard's c...
en


He gestured at the Golden Guard's cars behind us.

LineNo: 12677059,

Narrator: Sir. I'm afraid I cannot do that.
en


"Sir. I'm afraid I cannot do that."

LineNo: 12677161,

Narrator: Suddenly, I noticed a group of armo...
en


Suddenly, I noticed a group of armored vehicles passing by the street we weren't allowed on, driving in the direction of the House of Delegates.

LineNo: 12677263,

Narrator: The officer tried to assure us that...
en


The officer tried to assure us that it would take a few minutes at most before they could allow us to proceed.

LineNo: 12677365,

Narrator: After noticing the armored cars ahe...
en


After noticing the armored cars ahead, Titus talked to his radio and asked for a situation report.

LineNo: 12677467,

Titus Gordion: Your Majesty. There is something w...
en


"Your Majesty. There is something wrong."

LineNo: 12678959,

Titus Gordion: The capital security has been put...
en


"The capital security has been put on emergency mode by Duchess Azaro."

LineNo: 12679061,

Titus Gordion: The capital security has been put...
en


"The capital security has been put on emergency mode by General Azaro."

LineNo: 12679163,

Titus Gordion: The capital security has been put...
en


"The capital security has been put on emergency mode by Ricardus Toras."

LineNo: 12679265,

Titus Gordion: Apparently, a hundred trucks' wort...
en


"Apparently, a hundred trucks' worth of military equipment from Montaklar are being transferred to the capital right now."

LineNo: 12679367,

Titus Gordion: The police have been put on high a...
en


"The police have been put on high alert."

LineNo: 12679469,

Titus Gordion: The capital security has been put...
en


"The capital security has been put on emergency mode by Ricardus Toras."

LineNo: 12679571,

Titus Gordion: The police was put on high alert.
en


"The police was put on high alert."

LineNo: 12679673,

Titus Gordion: Apparently, a hundred trucks worth...
en


"Apparently, a hundred trucks worth of military equipment from Iza are being transferred to the capital security right now."

LineNo: 12680331,

Titus Gordion: Apparently, a hundred trucks worth...
en


"Apparently, a hundred trucks worth of military equipment from Monqiz are being transferred to the capital security right now."

LineNo: 12680433,

Titus Gordion: Apparently, hundreds of Su Omina m...
en


"Apparently, hundreds of Su Omina members have arrived. They are suspected to be carrying weapons."

LineNo: 12680813,

Titus Gordion: Apparently, a hundred trucks worth...
en


"Apparently, a hundred trucks worth of military equipment from Brenas are being transferred to the capital security right now."

LineNo: 12681749,

Titus Gordion: They must have been organizing sin...
en


"They must have been organizing since you announced the date of the constitutional reforms. I don't know how we didn't receive any intelligence of this before."

LineNo: 12681851,

Titus Gordion: Your rivals and key security perso...
en


"Your rivals and key security personnel were already being watched. I don't know how we didn't receive any intelligence of this beforehand."

LineNo: 12681953,

Titus Gordion: Somebody from the inside must have...
en


"Somebody from the inside must have shared the details of what's happening today. I don't know how we didn't receive any intelligence of this beforehand."

LineNo: 12682055,

Titus Gordion: This cannot be a coincidence. But...
en


"This cannot be a coincidence. But the police are trying to assure us everything is under control."

LineNo: 12682181,

Player_Romus: I should have known Rico would be...
en


"I should have known Rico would be behind something like this. I'll make him pay."

LineNo: 12682283,

Player_Romus: Titus. I don't think we can trust...
en


"Titus. I don't think we can trust any intelligence right now. Please take us to safety."

LineNo: 12682663,

Player_Romus: Just tell the convoy to keep drivi...
en


"Just tell the convoy to keep driving. I don't want to be pinned down on this small street."

LineNo: 12682765,

Player_Romus: I want you to be on high alert, Ti...
en


"I want you to be on high alert, Titus. I don't trust the police."

LineNo: 12682867,

Narrator: He nodded.
en


He nodded.

LineNo: 12682969,

Player_Romus: And what are those armored vehicle...
en


"And what are those armored vehicles doing inside the city?"

LineNo: 12683071,

Titus Gordion: They must be part of the police fo...
en


"They must be part of the police forces, sir. No military is allowed here."

LineNo: 12683173,

Titus Gordion: What are your orders, Your Majesty?
en


"What are your orders, Your Majesty?"

LineNo: 12683291,

Player_Romus: We will listen to the officer and...
en


"We will listen to the officer and wait here."

LineNo: 12683393,

Narrator: Titus nodded and immediately sent a...
en


Titus nodded and immediately sent a radio message to the whole convoy.

LineNo: 12683495,

Titus Gordion: As you wish, Your Majesty.
en


"As you wish, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 12683693,

Narrator: As soon as our drivers ignited the...
en


As soon as our drivers ignited the engines, the leading officers from the blockade came running, surrounding our cars.

LineNo: 12683795,

Narrator: They shouted at me that they couldn...
en


They shouted at me that they couldn't let me leave. There was a security risk.

LineNo: 12683897,

Titus Gordion: Move away from the vehicles or we...
en


"Move away from the vehicles or we will run you over."

LineNo: 12683999,

Narrator: The officers hesitated, retreating...
en


The officers hesitated, retreating slightly. Murmurs crackled through their radios as they conferred swiftly amongst themselves.

LineNo: 12684101,

Narrator: Suddenly, they pointed their guns d...
en


Suddenly, they pointed their guns directly at us.

LineNo: 12684219,

Player_Romus: STOP! THEY'RE GOING TO SHOOT!
en


"STOP! THEY'RE GOING TO SHOOT!"

LineNo: 12684321,

Player_Romus: FLOOR IT! NOW!
en


"FLOOR IT! NOW!"

LineNo: 12684423,

Narrator: As our convoy inched forward, the o...
en


As our convoy inched forward, the officers paced alongside with their shouts of "halt", still maintaining a tight perimeter around us.

LineNo: 12684525,

Player_Romus: TITUS! OPEN FIRE!
en


"TITUS! OPEN FIRE!"

LineNo: 12684627,

Narrator: Hearing my screams, the guards read...
en


Hearing my screams, the guards readied their weapons and started shooting. From my vantage point inside the vehicle, I could see the officers diving for cover.

LineNo: 12684729,

Narrator: And then, hell broke loose with gun...
en


And then, hell broke loose with gunshots erupting from each side.

LineNo: 12684831,

Narrator: For a split second, the driver's ey...
en


For a split second, the driver's eyes met mine in the rearview mirror as he nodded and slammed his foot on the gas pedal.

LineNo: 12684933,

Narrator: As we lurched forward, the officers...
en


As we lurched forward, the officers scrambled, trying to evade our vehicle.

LineNo: 12685035,

Narrator: Within a few seconds, the officers'...
en


Within a few seconds, the officers' widening eyes and their screams were swallowed by the roar of the engine.

LineNo: 12685137,

Narrator: After a minute or two, the armored...
en


After a minute or two, the armored vehicles we saw before also arrived on the street from the direction of the parliament.

LineNo: 12685239,

Narrator: As we tried to understand what was...
en


As we tried to understand what was going on, a military officer leapt atop one of the vehicles, grabbed a megaphone and made an announcement.

LineNo: 12685897,

Narrator: Abdicate the throne to Lucita Azar...
en


"Abdicate the throne to Lucita Azaro, and your life and noble status will be spared."

LineNo: 12686277,

Narrator: Abdicate the throne to Taddeus Aza...
en


"Abdicate the throne to Taddeus Azaro, and your life and noble status will be spared."

LineNo: 12686379,

Narrator: Abdicate the throne to Hugo Toras,...
en


"Abdicate the throne to Hugo Toras, and your life and noble status will be spared."

LineNo: 12686481,

Narrator: Abdicate the throne to Ricardus To...
en


"Abdicate the throne to Ricardus Toras, and your life and noble status will be spared."

LineNo: 12686967,

Narrator: Romus Toras. You are surrounded.
en


"Romus Toras. You are surrounded."

LineNo: 12687069,

Narrator: You are under arrest for conspirin...
en


"You are under arrest for conspiring against the Rizian monarchy and the very title you hold."

LineNo: 12687171,

Narrator: For attempting to dismantle the Ri...
en


"For attempting to dismantle the Rizian monarchy, traitor Manus Sazon and the members of the Rizian People's Party have been arrested."

LineNo: 12687273,

Narrator: As his words echoed, I felt fear cr...
en


As his words echoed, I felt fear creep up in me.

LineNo: 12687375,

Titus Gordion: Your Majesty!
en


"Your Majesty!"

LineNo: 12687477,

Titus Gordion: What are your orders?
en


"What are your orders?"

LineNo: 12687595,

Player_Romus: OPEN FIRE! NOW!
en


"OPEN FIRE! NOW!"

LineNo: 12687703,

Player_Romus: I need to do as they say.
en


"I need to do as they say."

LineNo: 12687811,

Player_Romus: There is nothing we can do, Titus....
en


"There is nothing we can do, Titus. I have to comply."

LineNo: 12687919,

Titus Gordion: But sir!
en


"But sir!"

LineNo: 12688021,

Narrator: Hearing my screams, the driver slam...
en


Hearing my screams, the driver slammed his foot on the brake pedal.

LineNo: 12688123,

Narrator: Within a few seconds, the officers...
en


Within a few seconds, the officers quickly surrounded our vehicle and took us outside.

LineNo: 12688409,

Narrator: They pinned us down and with a clin...
en


They pinned us down and with a clink of metal handcuffs, they secured our wrists.

LineNo: 12688541,

Player_Romus: What the hell are you doing? I am...
en


"What the hell are you doing? I am your King!"

LineNo: 12688643,

Player_Romus: You must have mistaken me for some...
en


"You must have mistaken me for someone else."

LineNo: 12689015,

Player_Romus: Take your hands off me!
en


"Take your hands off me!"

LineNo: 12689117,

Player_Romus: We are not resisting. This is not...
en


"We are not resisting. This is not necessary."

LineNo: 12689219,

Player_Romus: We are not resisting. This is not...
en


"We are not resisting. This is not necessary."

LineNo: 12689327,

Player_Romus: I am not a common criminal. Take t...
en


"I am not a common criminal. Take these off of me!"

LineNo: 12689435,

Player_Romus: Please don't hurt my family.
en


"Please don't hurt my family."

LineNo: 12689543,

Player_Romus: One day, you will pay for this.
en


"One day, you will pay for this."

LineNo: 12689651,

Narrator: They did not react to what I said....
en


They did not react to what I said. They simply smiled as they disarmed my guards.

LineNo: 12689879,

Narrator: I left the vehicle.
en


I left the vehicle.

LineNo: 12689987,

Narrator: They quickly pinned me down and wit...
en


They quickly pinned me down and with a clink of metal handcuffs, and secured my wrists.

LineNo: 12690095,

Narrator: They did not react. They quickly di...
en


They did not react. They quickly disarmed the rest of my guards. The officer spoke to me.

LineNo: 12690197,

Narrator: For attempting to dismantle the Ri...
en


"For attempting to dismantle the Rizian monarchy, Manus Sazon and the traitors of the Rizian People's Party have been arrested."

LineNo: 12690299,

Narrator: And you, Romus Toras, are under ar...
en


"And you, Romus Toras, are under arrest for conspiring against the Rizian monarchy and the very title you hold."

LineNo: 12690425,

Player_Romus: I am under WHAT?
en


"I am under WHAT?"

LineNo: 12690527,

Player_Romus: Gentlemen! This is Rizian justice...
en


"Gentlemen! This is Rizian justice manifest!"

LineNo: 12690629,

Player_Romus: One day, you will pay for this.
en


"One day, you will pay for this."

LineNo: 12690737,

Player_Romus_Italic: I stayed silent.
en


I stayed silent.

LineNo: 12690743,

Player_Romus_Italic: I stayed silent.
Menu Text en


Stay silent.

LineNo: 12690845,

Narrator: They grabbed me by my arms and shov...
en


They grabbed me by my arms and shoved me into a police truck.

LineNo: 12690947,

Narrator: I had no idea where they were takin...
en


I had no idea where they were taking me.

LineNo: 12693121,

Narrator: Within just a second, hell broke lo...
en


Within just a second, hell broke loose around me with gunshots erupting from each side. I threw myself on the floor of the vehicle.

LineNo: 12693223,

Narrator: Hearing my screams, the guards read...
en


Hearing my screams, the guards readied their weapons and started shooting. From my vantage point inside the vehicle, I could see the officers diving for cover.

LineNo: 12693325,

Narrator: Before any of us could react, there...
en


Before any of us could react, there was a deafening explosion.

LineNo: 12693427,

Narrator: The engine of our vehicle roared as...
en


The engine of our vehicle roared as the driver hit the gas pedal. We quickly drove among the sounds of Kalsingtons being fired from every direction.

LineNo: 12693529,

Narrator: The world outside became a blur of...
en


The world outside became a blur of motion and noise. Bullets pinged against the armored exterior of the vehicle as we drove down the street.

LineNo: 12693631,

Titus Gordion: We can't go back to the palace now...
en


"We can't go back to the palace now. Take us the emergency bunker!"

LineNo: 12693733,

Narrator: The streets became a labyrinthine e...
en


The streets became a labyrinthine escape route, as we navigated through them with great speed.

LineNo: 12693835,

Narrator: In the aftermath of our escape, as...
en


In the aftermath of our escape, as we put distance between ourselves and the rebels, I let out a deep sigh.

LineNo: 12693937,

Narrator: I had survived this attack. But my...
en


I had survived this attack. But my usurper was still out there.
